For METAFONTbook p.39, run in /tmp:
  If you will view (tex+ testfont):
    mf '\mode=screen; mag=4; input io'
  If you will print (tex- testfont):
    mf '\mode=localfont; mag=4; input io'
  Local system wizard does this:
    cp io.tfm ~/tex/TeXfonts/
    ~/gftopk/gftopk <resulting GF> <PK location from ~/mf/Makefile>/<mode>/<GF as PK> /dev/stdout
  Running 'make' here will clean up ~/tex/TeXfonts/ and PK location

----------------------------------------------------------

For METAFONTbook p.245, run:
  /bin/mf 13-24
